PHP in the Dark is a workshop that talks about PHP in a non-web context. It is divided in 4 parts:

1) shell scripting: simple command line bash scripts. How to use, how to work with input and output, specific tools, etc...

2) daemons: explains how to properly set up a daemon, work with signals, etc...

3) intraprocess communication: discusses communication between processes, queues, "multi-threading", etc...

4) process distribution: spread the work over multiple servers

The talk is available as a two to three hour workshop or as 2 one hour talks.

